OL,7,FSitting at home plugged into his
OL,8,Fdialysis machine, Andy Quin knows the
OL,9,Felectricity needed to power the
OL,10,Fcontraption really is a matter of life
OL,11,Fand death.
OL,13,F"If I don't use dialysis for a few
OL,14,Fweeks, I'm gone, I'm dead, that's the
OL,15,Fstark reality," he tells i. "But it's
OL,16,Fnot just the machine that costs kidney
OL,17,Fpatients having dialysis at home, but
OL,18,Fthe heating and lighting in the room
OL,19,Fwhile they do it for hours at a time,
OL,20,Fseveral times a week."
